    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-11-15T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-11-15T19:00:00-05:00" n="1692"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1692">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">119.2/10–2949: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Second Secretary of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bacon</hi>
                    </persName>), <hi rend="italic">at Nanking</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-11-15T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 15, 1949—7 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1234. Urtel 2330, Oct 29. Trans[fer] radio equipment Commies prohibited by
                    reg[ulation]s and in accordance Depcirtel Sep 14, para 4M.<note n="67"
                        xml:id="d1692fn67">See footnote 66, <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>
                    </note> Although refcirtel intended as general Admin instr all China posts, it
                    was not sent Tihwa view earlier closure that office. Therefore, probable Brit
                    Con Tihwa not aware provision that radio equipment shld not be allowed fall into
                    Commie hands intact.</p>
                <p>In discussing matter with Brit Emb you may point out that obviously Commies wld
                    use radio equipment to further anti-Amer propaganda. If radio equipment not
                    already mutilated and inexpedient do so now, and if Commies arbitrarily seize,
                    inform Dept.</p>
                <p>Dept leaves to ur discretion in consultation Brit Emb nature reply to be sent
                    Brit Con Tihwa. Brit Emb Wash informs Dept Brit Con Tihwa desires instr in plain
                    text, via commercial channels.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Webb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
